snippet: U.S. and Japanese trade negotiators have been unable to reach a deal to open Japan's markets more widely to imports ahead of President Barack Obama's visit to Japan, a senior U.S. administration official said on Friday....

headline.print_headline: Trade Deal Eluding U.S., Japan, Senior U.S. Official Says
headline.main: Trade Deal Eluding U.S., Japan, Senior U.S. Official Says

lead_paragraph: U.S. and Japanese trade negotiators have been unable to reach a deal to open Japan's markets more widely to imports ahead of President Barack Obama's visit to Japan, a senior U.S. administration official said on Friday.
